  "text": "Regarding issues to users' anonymity, a recent study has demonstrated that pseudonyms chosen by users at different websites can be linked to deduce their real identity [CITATION_1] . This probability of linking and profiling users could increase if users' pseudonyms can be identified based on their lock pattern behavior when authenticating into different services. Yet another study has shown that users' identities can be reconstructed from their typing patterns while browsing online [CITATION_2] . In our paper, we consider if similar issues can arise when employing the biometrics of lock patterns for authentication.",
